comments.content:
@Tiffany: type vs. typography

Hm. Just went back and re-read that. I'm probably equating the two in my analogies.

I remember arguing that point with Hrant once on Typographica, that I thought lettering should be included under the tent of typography. Now I'm not so sure. If "typography" means "the craft and art of letter forms", then lettering should be included. If "typography" means "the craft and art of type", then, no.

@Will - That is a nice analogy. But I maintain that as the lettering artist works they are kerning, spacing, line-spacing, column-width adjusting... albeit "on the fly".

I still think some of you aren't separating type from typography.

One could argue that typefaces are sculpture too, but I buy the sculptures pre-made and use them as they are. ;)
